Four people were killed and 21 others injured on Thursday after two taxis collided head-on on the R26, outside of Ladybrand in the Free State.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said one of the taxi was found on the emergency lane while the other was found on the side of the road. Upon arrival, ER24 paramedics found that two taxis had collided head on. One taxi was found in the emergency lane of the road while the larger taxi was found on the side of the road, both vehicles had sustained a large amount of damage in the collision said Meiring.Paramedics on the scene found that the drivers of the taxis, both men, were trapped inside of their vehicles and showed no signs of life.&#8220;Unfortunately, both men had already succumbed to their multiple fatal injuries,nothing could be done for the men and they were declared dead on the scene&#8221;,Meiring said.Four other patients were found lying trapped inside of the taxis while several other patients were found walking around on the scene.Meiring added that rescue services had to use the jaws of life equipment to free the trapped passengers. The paramedics found that 20 people had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate while two others had been left in a critical condition.Critically injured patients were treated with advanced life support interventions before they were transported to nearby hospitals for urgent treatment.&#8220;Unfortunately, upon arrival at hospital, one of the critically injured patients, a woman, succumbed to her injuries and was pronounced dead at hospital&#8221;, Meiring said.The cause of the collision is yet to be determined however local authorities were on scene for further investigations.&nbsp;-TNA Reporter